    <div class="row demo-row" id="faq">
      <div class="span12">
        <div class="demo-text-box prl">
          <h1>Frequently asked questions</h1>
          <p>Here are the questions we hear most often about the program.</p>
          <br>
          <p><strong>Are you also looking for mentors and projects for the program?</strong></p>
          <p>Yes. Mentors must have experience with applied data science projects. You’ll help scope projects, lead a team, and mentor fellows.</p>
          <p>If you’re qualified, <a href="mailto:datasciencefellowship@ci.uchicago.edu">contact us</a> - we have full-time, paid mentor positions available We can always use more volunteer mentors as well.</p>
          <br>
          <p><strong>Can I do the fellowship in the evening or part-time?</strong></p>
          <p>No. We expect fellows to work on these projects full-time during the summer.</p>
          <br>
          <p><strong>Do I physically need to be in Chicago?</strong></p>
          <p>Yes.</p>
          <br>
          <p><strong>I’m on an F-1/J-1 visa. Can I apply?</strong></p>
          <p>Yes. If you’re authorized to work and get paid by us, you’re eligible to apply.</p>
          <br>
          <p><strong>I’m not a US citizen or permanent resident. Can I apply?</strong></p>
          <p>If you’re able to get a visa that allows you to work in the US for the summer - and get paid by us - you can apply.</p>    
          <br>
        </div>
